      "side": 1,
      "message": "it does, but cl.Snapshot will be loaded anyway from datastore as part of loadCLs, it ought to be the same Snapshot.\n\nNote also that prjmanager itself doesn\u0027t store Snapshots, only the run.Trigger.\nHence, prjmanager will effectively need to load CL twice:\n  1. Decide to start a run based on (triggerInfo + basic CL metadata)\n  2. Load snapshots \n  3. Init RunBuilder using data from #2.\n  4. RunBuilder.Create()\n  4.1. LoadCLs\n  4.2. Write RunCLs with snapshots.\n\nThe #2 is only needed for compat with CQDaemon.",
